<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>SPICER 14-INCH (355.6 MM) STAMPED ANGLE-SPRING CLUTCH - SINGLE PLATE CLUTCH REMOVAL - CLUTCH REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>CLUTCH REMOVAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the spline aligning tool into the release bearing assembly and driven disc. An old
                transmission input shaft may be used for this purpose (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100308">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1100307" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100307" filename="../figg11/G1100307.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. Disconnect External Clutch Linkage</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100308" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100308" filename="../figg11/G1100308.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 8. Install Spline Aligning Tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert two 1 1/2" spacers between the flywheel ring and the release bearing housing. Spacers
                relieve the heavy internal spring load in the clutch assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100309">Figure 9</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100310">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Because of the weight of a 14" clutch, install two guide studs in the top mounting bolt
                holes to facilitate removal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100310">Figure 10</hotlnk>). Loosen the mounting bolts around the flywheel in a
                criss-cross pattern to prevent cocking and bending of the clutch mounting bolts.
                <emph type="bold">Do not remove the bolts.</emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After all the bolts are loose, remove the mounting bolts and carefully remove the clutch
                assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100311">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1100309" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100309" filename="../figg11/G1100309.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Insert Spacers Between Flywheel Ring and Release Bearing Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100310" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100310" filename="../figg11/G1100310.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. Install Guide Studs</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100311" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100311" filename="../figg11/G1100311.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. Remove Clutch Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100312" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100312" filename="../figg11/G1100312.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 12. Remove Spline Aligning Tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spline aligning tool and driven disc (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100312">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
